Steps -

1. create a new repository.
    -- Go to Integrate and select New git repository.
    
2. whenever you create a repository is by default first commit.

3. There is a changes in project then you have to commit.
    -- Go to Integrate and select commit.
    
4.Create a new Branch.
    -- Right click on current repository and select new Branch give name for that repository.

5.Merge a code between two repository.
    -- The current branch is always the branch you want to merge into.
    -- Right click 

5. command + up arrow + . to see the Hidden folder.
